Daily Schedule for an Engineering Manager
7:30 AM – 8:00 AM: Morning Routine & Preparation
Start the day with a quick review of emails, messages, and calendar for any urgent updates.
Prioritize tasks based on the day’s goals and focus areas.
8:00 AM – 9:00 AM: Focus Time (Deep Work)
Block out this time for critical thinking tasks, such as strategic planning, roadmap reviews, or technical design decisions.
Use this uninterrupted time to tackle high-priority tasks requiring focus.
9:00 AM – 9:30 AM: Daily Standup / Team Sync
Attend or run the team’s daily standup.
Get quick updates from the team, identify blockers, and ensure alignment on ongoing work.
9:30 AM – 10:30 AM: 1-on-1 Meetings
Use this slot for scheduled 1-on-1s with direct reports.
Focus on mentorship, feedback, and discussing their professional growth.
Address any team member concerns and remove blockers.
10:30 AM – 11:00 AM: Review & Plan
Review engineering metrics, sprint progress, or team performance dashboards.
Plan any necessary actions based on the current sprint status and ongoing projects.
11:00 AM – 12:00 PM: Cross-Functional Collaboration
Meet with other departments such as Product, Design, or Operations to align on project requirements or priorities.
Attend any leadership syncs or cross-team discussions.
12:00 PM – 1:00 PM: Lunch & Break
Take a break for lunch.
Use this time to recharge mentally, away from work.
1:00 PM – 2:30 PM: Code Reviews & Technical Discussions
Review pull requests, engage in technical discussions, or provide feedback on architectural decisions.
Stay engaged with the team's technical work without micromanaging.
2:30 PM – 3:30 PM: Project Management & Sprint Review
Review the sprint backlog, plan future work, and address any upcoming deadlines.
Collaborate with the Scrum Master to ensure that the team is on track for delivery.
Prepare for upcoming sprint meetings if needed.
3:30 PM – 4:00 PM: Open Office Hours for Team
Allow time for informal conversations with the team.
Be available to address any ad-hoc questions, issues, or coaching moments.
4:00 PM – 5:00 PM: Strategic Planning & Personal Development
Dedicate this time for high-level strategy or long-term planning (roadmaps, team growth, or tech debt).
Use some of this time for personal development: reading, learning, or reviewing industry trends.
5:00 PM – 5:30 PM: End-of-Day Wrap-Up
Review the day’s work, respond to remaining emails or messages.
Create a to-do list or goals for the next day.
Log progress or blockers for personal reference.
5:30 PM: Close Work & Unwind
Disconnect from work to recharge for the next day.
